The Chief Operating Officer of Lets Talk I.T & Telecommunications Company, Folashade Ayeni, has said the firm has concluded plans to launch Nigeria’s first instant messaging application, ‘Lets Talk’, which will be unveiled before the end of the third quarter of 2022.  Ayeni further disclosed that the company was aiming to collaborate with NITDA, the Nigerian Communications Commission (NCC) and other relevant agencies to ensure the success of the application and acceptability by Nigerians.
  
Speaking on the unique features of the app, she said it is end-to-encrypted, allows users to listen and share music, video and audio call, 5,000 member group chat, seven person conference calls and file exchange up to 2GB.
  
She said: “It also allows for device and cloud caching as well as sharing moments and trends which will give users very pleasant experiences. The application could be downloaded on Google Play and App Store for both android and Apple phones.” 